Vice President Mike Pence delivered remarks at Parkdale Mills in Monroe, North Carolina, highlighting the successes of the Trump administration in revitalizing the American economy and manufacturing industry. Pence praised the company and its employees for their contributions to American manufacturing and emphasized the importance of passing the United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement (USMCA) to further strengthen the economy. He also criticized Democrats in Congress for prioritizing politics over progress. Pence urged the audience to voice their support for the USMCA and encouraged elected officials to do their job and pass the trade deal. He concluded by promising to continue fighting for the policies that have revived the economy and made America prosperous.